2:03 PM Defendant Brytni F Anderson in court in custody.  Attorney Obi Uzowulu in court for Brytni F Anderson.  Attorney Samuel Berg in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant enters a plea of guilty to both counts contained in the criminal complaint.
Court has a colloquy with defendant.
Court gives WARNINGS regarding deportation, felon prohibited from firearm possession pursuant to Sec. 941.29, and ineligibility to vote until civil rights restored.
Attorney Uzowulu believes pleas to be made freely, knowingly, and voluntarily.
Plea questionnaire/waiver of rights filed. Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and adjudges defendant guilty.

Court goes over sentencing factors.
Court imposes:

WITHHELD SENTENCE, defendant placed on Probation for a period of four (4) years.  Probation may transfer to Missouri if arrangements can be made.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:

Twelve (12) months in Jail.  First four (4) months are WITHOUT work release on Count 1, balance to be with work release and defendant may have electronic monitoring for this portion of sentence, if found eligible.
Forty-three (43) days dead time credit, if probation is revoked.
Costs only on both counts, including any supervision fees.
Restitution is held open.
No alcohol.
No recreational drugs or drug paraphernalia.
Take any prescription medications as prescribed in therapeutic amounts.
Complete AODA and follow through with any recommendations.
Complete any other counseling as recommended by agent.
Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge.
Scheduling Order will be provided to Attys via e-filing by the Court
